[{"t":"MCAdvertiserAssistant","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCAdvertiserAssistant","r":"Class","a":"The `MCAdvertiserAssistant` is a convenience class that handles advertising, presents incoming invitations to the user, and handles users\u2019 responses. Use this class to provide a user interface for handling invitations when your app does not require programmatic control over the invitation process.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCAdvertiserAssistantDelegate","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCAdvertiserAssistantDelegate","r":"Protocol","a":"The `MCAdvertiserAssistantDelegate` protocol describes the methods that the delegate object for an `MCAdvertiserAssistant` instance can implement to handle advertising-related events.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCBrowserViewController","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCBrowserViewController","r":"Class","a":"The `MCBrowserViewController` class presents nearby devices to the user and enables the user to invite nearby devices to a session. To use this class in iOS or tvOS, call methods from the underlying `UIViewController` class ([prepare(for:sender:)](/documentation/UIKit/UIViewController/prepare(for:sender:)) and [performSegue(withIdentifier:sender:)](/documentation/UIKit/UIViewController/performSegue(withIdentifier:sender:)) for storyboards or [present(_:animated:completion:)](/documentation/UIKit/UIViewController/present(_:animated:completion:)) and [dismiss(animated:completion:)](/documentation/UIKit/UIViewController/dismiss(animated:completion:)) for nib-based views) to present and dismiss the view controller. In macOS, use the comparable `NSViewController` methods [presentAsSheet(_:)](/documentation/AppKit/NSViewController/presentAsSheet(_:)) and [dismiss(_:)](/documentation/AppKit/NSViewController/dismiss(_:)-91my5) instead.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCBrowserViewControllerDelegate","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCBrowserViewControllerDelegate","r":"Protocol","a":"The `MCBrowserViewControllerDelegate` protocol defines the methods that your delegate object can implement to handle events related to the `MCBrowserViewController` class.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCEncryptionPreference","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCEncryptionPreference","r":"Enumeration","a":"Indicates whether a session should use encryption when communicating with nearby peers.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCEncryptionPreference.none","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCEncryptionPreference/none","r":"Case","a":"The session should not be encrypted.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCEncryptionPreference.optional","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCEncryptionPreference/optional","r":"Case","a":"The session prefers to use encryption, but accepts unencrypted connections. A connection uses encryption when all the peers choose either [MCEncryptionPreference.optional](/documentation/multipeerconnectivity/mcencryptionpreference/optional) or [MCEncryptionPreference.required](/documentation/multipeerconnectivity/mcencryptionpreference/required). If some peers choose [MCEncryptionPreference.none](/documentation/multipeerconnectivity/mcencryptionpreference/none), then the session will not be encrypted. For this reason, if some peers running your app can be configured without encryption, you should always assume that the session is unencrypted.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCEncryptionPreference.required","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCEncryptionPreference/required","r":"Case","a":"The session requires encryption.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCError","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCError","r":"Structure","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCError.Code","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCError/Code","r":"Enumeration","a":"Error codes found in [MCErrorDomain](/documentation/multipeerconnectivity/mcerrordomain) error domain `NSError` objects returned by methods in the Multipeer Connectivity framework.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCError.Code.cancelled","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCError/Code/cancelled","r":"Case","a":"The operation was cancelled by the user.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCError.Code.invalidParameter","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCError/Code/invalidParameter","r":"Case","a":"Your app passed an invalid value as a parameter.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCError.Code.notConnected","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCError/Code/notConnected","r":"Case","a":"Your app attempted to send data to a peer that is not connected.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCError.Code.timedOut","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCError/Code/timedOut","r":"Case","a":"The connection attempt timed out.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCError.Code.unavailable","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCError/Code/unavailable","r":"Case","a":"Multipeer connectivity is currently unavailable.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCError.Code.unknown","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCError/Code/unknown","r":"Case","a":"An unknown error occurred.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCError.Code.unsupported","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCError/Code/unsupported","r":"Case","a":"The operation is unsupported. For example, this error is returned if you call [sendResource(at:withName:toPeer:withCompletionHandler:)](/documentation/multipeerconnectivity/mcsession/sendresource(at:withname:topeer:withcompletionhandler:)) with a URL that is neither a local file nor a web URL.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCErrorDomain","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCErrorDomain","r":"Global Variable","a":"The `NSError` domain constant. If the `domain` value for an `NSError` object is equal to `MCErrorDomain`, then the error was produced by the Multipeer Connectivity framework itself, as opposed to a lower-level framework on which it depends.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCNearbyServiceAdvertiser","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCNearbyServiceAdvertiser","r":"Class","a":"The `MCNearbyServiceAdvertiser` class publishes an advertisement for a specific service that your app provides through the Multipeer Connectivity framework and notifies its delegate about invitations from nearby peers.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCNearbyServiceAdvertiserDelegate","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCNearbyServiceAdvertiserDelegate","r":"Protocol","a":"The `MCNearbyServiceAdvertiserDelegate` protocol describes the methods that the delegate object for an `MCNearbyServiceAdvertiser` instance can implement for handling events from the `MCNearbyServiceAdvertiser` class.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCNearbyServiceBrowser","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCNearbyServiceBrowser","r":"Class","a":"Searches (by service type) for services offered by nearby devices using infrastructure Wi-Fi, peer-to-peer Wi-Fi, and Bluetooth (in iOS) or Ethernet (in macOS and tvOS), and provides the ability to easily invite those devices to a Multipeer Connectivity session (`MCSession`).","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCNearbyServiceBrowserDelegate","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCNearbyServiceBrowserDelegate","r":"Protocol","a":"The `MCNearbyServiceBrowserDelegate` protocol defines methods that a `MCNearbyServiceBrowser` object\u2019s delegate can implement to handle browser-related events.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCPeerID","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCPeerID","r":"Class","a":"An  `MCPeerID` object represents a peer in a multipeer session.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCSession","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCSession","r":"Class","a":"An `MCSession` object enables and manages communication among all peers in a Multipeer Connectivity session.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCSessionDelegate","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCSessionDelegate","r":"Protocol","a":"The `MCSessionDelegate` protocol defines methods that a delegate of the `MCSession` class can implement to handle session-related events. For more information, see [MCSession](/documentation/multipeerconnectivity/mcsession).","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCSessionSendDataMode","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCSessionSendDataMode","r":"Enumeration","a":"Indicates whether delivery of data should be guaranteed.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCSessionSendDataMode.reliable","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCSessionSendDataMode/reliable","r":"Case","a":"The framework should guarantee delivery of each message, enqueueing and retransmitting data as needed, and ensuring in-order delivery.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCSessionSendDataMode.unreliable","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCSessionSendDataMode/unreliable","r":"Case","a":"Messages to peers should be sent immediately without socket-level queueing. If a message cannot be sent immediately, it should be dropped. The order of messages is not guaranteed.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCSessionState","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCSessionState","r":"Enumeration","a":"Indicates the current state of a given peer within a session.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCSessionState.connected","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCSessionState/connected","r":"Case","a":"The peer is connected to this session.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCSessionState.connecting","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCSessionState/connecting","r":"Case","a":"A connection to the peer is currently being established.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MCSessionState.notConnected","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCSessionState/notConnected","r":"Case","a":"The peer is not (or is no longer) in this session.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.1","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MC_EXTERN","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MC_EXTERN","r":"Macro","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.0","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MC_EXTERN_CLASS","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MC_EXTERN_CLASS","r":"Macro","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.0","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"MC_EXTERN_WEAK","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MC_EXTERN_WEAK","r":"Macro","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.0","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"Minimum and Maximum Supported Peers","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/minimum_and_maximum_supported_peers","r":"API Collection","a":"Constants that define the minimum and maximum number of peers supported in a session."},{"t":"Multipeer Connectivity","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity","r":"Framework","a":"Support peer-to-peer connectivity and the discovery of nearby devices.","v":{"iOS":"7.0","iPadOS":"7.0","Mac Catalyst":"13.0","macOS":"10.10","tvOS":"10.0","visionOS":"1.0"}},{"t":"Multipeer Connectivity Error Domain","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/multipeer_connectivity_error_domain","r":"API Collection","a":"The error domain for errors specific to Multipeer Connectivity."},{"t":"MultipeerConnectivity Constants","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/multipeerconnectivity_constants","r":"API Collection"},{"t":"MultipeerConnectivity Enumerations","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/multipeerconnectivity_enumerations","r":"API Collection"},{"t":"advertiser(_:didNotStartAdvertisingPeer:)","p":"documentation/MultipeerConnectivity/MCNearbyServiceAdvertiserDelegate/advertiser(_:didNotStartAdvertisingPeer:)","r":"Instance Method